Backend Setup:

Clone the Repository
https://github.com/shivanis123/Product_Management.git
cd Backend-aws

Install Dependencies

npm install
Set Up Environment Variables
Create a .env file in the root of the backend directory with the following content:

env
PORT=5001
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret_key
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your_aws_access_key_id
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your_aws_secret_access_key
AWS_REGION=your_aws_region

Start the Backend Server
nodemon server.js

Frontend Setup:

Navigate to the Frontend Directory
cd frontend

Install Dependencies
npm install

Start the Frontend Development Server
npm start

Accessing the Application
Backend: The backend server will be running on http://localhost:5001.
Frontend: The frontend application will be running on http://localhost:3000.

Usage
Admin Login: Navigate to /login to log in as an admin.
Product Management: After logging in, navigate to /products to view, create, edit, or delete products. Use the search and filter functionalities to find specific products.
